KIMBERLEY - One SA Police Service (SAPS) officer was shot dead and two others were injured in a shootout with a man on Tuesday afternoon.According to SAPS spokesperson Colonel Mohale Ramatseba, the shooter went to the local police station looking for his wife, with the intention of attacking her.READ: TMPD officer charged with murderWhen he could not find her there he drove away and got into an altercation with police at the corner of Long and Lennox road.The man and the officers exchanged gunfire and one police member as well as the suspect were fatally wounded and died at the scene.Two SAPS members who were injured were transported to a nearby hospital.The suspect was reportedly a former police officer. eNCA